Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. 

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel). Pop onto a 
large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, 
then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer. 

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the middle shelf until golden, ~{30-40%mins}. 
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, trim the @green beans{150%grams}. Grate the @mature Cheddar cheese{40%grams}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine the @tomato puree{30%grams}, 
@sun-dried tomato paste{25%grams}, @sugar{1/2%tsp} and 
@water{1%tbsp} for the sauce. Mix well together and set aside.

Crack the @egg{1} into a #medium bowl{} and whisk.

Put the @breadcrumbs{50%grams} into another bowl and season with the 
@salt{1/4%tsp} and pepper.

Sandwich each @British chicken breasts{2} between two pieces of 
#baking paper{} or #cling film{}.

Pop onto a #board{}, then give it a bash with a #rolling pin{} or the bottom 
of a #saucepan{} until it's 1-2cm thick. Season with salt and pepper.

Dip the chicken into the egg and then the breadcrumbs, ensuring it's 
completely coated. Transfer to a clean #plate{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its 
> packaging and discard any excess egg.

Pop a large #frying pan{} on high heat and add enough @oil{} to coat the bottom 
of the pan.

> TIP: You want the oil to be hot so the chicken fries properly - heat for 2-3 
> mins before you add the chicken.

Once hot, carefully lay the chicken into the pan and fry until golden brown, 
~{2-3%mins} on each side. Adjust the heat if necessary.

Transfer the chicken to a baking tray and bake on the middle shelf of your oven 
until cooked through, ~{8-10%mins}. Discard the oil from the chicken pan.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, wipe out the (now empty) frying pan and pop back on medium high heat 
with a drizzle of @oil{}.

Once hot, add the green beans and stir-fry until starting to char, 
~{2-3%mins}.

Turn the heat down to medium, then add a splash of @water{1%splash} and 
immediately cover with a #lid{} or some #foil{}. Cook until tender, 
~{4-5%mins}.

Remove the pan from the heat.

Once the chicken is cooked, remove from the oven and spread the tomato sauce 
mixture on top followed by the cheese. Return to the oven to bake until the 
cheese has melted, ~{2-3%mins}.

When everything's ready, share the chicken parm, roast potatoes and beans 
between your plates.

Serve with a dollop of @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} alongside for dipping. Enjoy!